resources.string:
The Available Card Sets screen is the "main menu" for PPP for Android. From this screen, you may select any of the card sets stored in your database, as well as add, modify, and delete card sets. This is also your launching point for accessing individual PPP cards.

At the top of the screen is a New or "plus" button. Tap this button to create a new card set. Alternatively, you may also tap Menu then New to accomplish the same task. Either action will launch the New Card Set screen, where you can specify the parameters for the new card set.

The main body of the screen is a scrolling list of all card sets in the database. The card sets are listed alphabetically. Tapping on a card set name launches the Card View screen by default, which is where you will view individual cards and generate passcodes. You may tap Back from the Card View screen to return to the Available Card Sets screen.

If you "long press" a card set name, you will launch a context menu dialog. From this menu, you can perform the following actions:

Details: Launches the Card Set Details screen, where you can view the card set's parameters in read-only mode;

Rename: Opens a dialog box where you can assign a new name to the selected card set;

Clear Strikes: Deletes all "strike out" data in the database for the selected card set, but leaves all other parameters intact;

Delete: Deletes the card set and all "strike out" data from the database.

The Clear Strikes and Delete options will display a confirmation dialog before these actions are performed.

Tapping the Menu button on your device provides the following additional options:

New: Launches the New Card Set screen to create a new card set;

Delete All: Deletes all card set data from the database, which cannot be undone (a confirmation dialog is displayed before this action is performed);

Settings: Launches the Settings screen, where you can set a password or configure additional options;

Help: Displays this help screen;

About: Displays copyright, credits, version, licensing information about PPP for Android.

The Card Set Details screen provides a read-only display of the parameters defining the selected card set, as well as a few statistics. It displays:

* The card set name;
* The last card displayed;
* The total number of "strike outs";
* The number of rows and columns;
* The passcode length;
* The alphabet used for passcode generation;
* The unencrypted sequence key.

The sequence key is always displayed in its unencrypted from here. If you set a password to protect PPP for Android from unauthorized access, the sequence key will remain encrypted in the database but will be decrypted on the fly to be displayed here.

Tapping the Menu button on your device displays the following options:

View Last Card: Launches the Card View screen displaying the last card in the set that was displayed;

Rename: Opens a dialog box where you can specify a new display name for the card set;

Clear Strikes: Deletes all "strike out" data from the database for this card set but leaves all other parameters intact;

Delete: Deletes the card set and all "strike out" data from the database, which cannot be undone;

Help: Displays this help screen.

The Clear Strikes and Delete options display a confirmation dialog before these actions are performed. Tapping the Back button on your device returns you to the previous screen.
